BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:Ed4vdAVmgx7GLAN-j5u_4
SUMMARY:Earth Month Event | Restoration at Ellis Pond
DTSTAMP:20260404T044000Z
DTSTART:20260411T163000Z
DESCRIPTION:Celebrate Earth Month at our Ellis Pond Work Party\n\nJoin us  
	at Ellis Pond Park for a Forest-Steward led weeding and clean-up event fo 
	r Earth Month. Removing certain plants will help build even more wildlife 
	 habitat in this small neighborhood park teeming with birds and other wood
	l and creatures. We will remove weeds like English ivy\, Himalayan blackbe
	rry\, and English holly to help protect native plants and forest health. C
	ome join friends and neighbors in this fun Saturday event.  \n\nNo experie
	 nce necessary\; gloves and tools are provided. Participation is limited\,
	 so please register.\n\nPlease note: we require participants aged 14 and  
	under to volunteer with a parent or guardian at a ratio of 1 adult to 3 ki
	 ds.\n\nWhen: Saturday\, April 11th\, 9:30am-11:30pm\n\nWhere: Ellis Pond 
	Park \\(meet at the bench next to the boardwalk on 90th Ave SE\\)\n\nWhat 
	to bring:  Dress for the weather in clothes you don't mind getting dirty \
	\(think: lon g pants\, boots or sneakers\\). Bring a water bottle. Small s
	nacks\, gloves\, and tools will be provided. And a snack or dish to share.
	 \n\nRegistration : volunteersignup.org/Y8XQX\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.
	com/events/#/details/earth-month-event-restoration-at-ellis-pond/18066408/
	2026-04-11T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Community & Civic
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/earth-month-event-restora
	tion-at-ellis-pond/18066408/2026-04-11T00
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-community
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Community & Civic
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
